 DemoEdgeStyle connected
 EWC.CONNECTED←connected
 ⎕PW←1000

⍝ EdgeStyle + Border Demo
⍝
⍝ Demonstrates the two INDEPENDENT properties side-by-side across the five
⍝ supported components: Edit, Label, List, Group, SubForm.
⍝
⍝   EdgeStyle: rich style — Ridge|Groove|Recess|Plinth|Shadow|None
⍝   Border:    yes/no toggle — 0 = no border, 1 = plain 1px border
⍝
⍝ Each row is one component. Each column is one property combination, with
⍝ a header above the column. The two trailing columns (B=1+Ridge, B=1+None)
⍝ exercise the case where both properties are set, which is the behaviour
⍝ that was previously coupled in the client.
⍝
⍝ Stable IDs let e2e tests target individual cells:
⍝   F1.{E|L|LST|G|SF}_{Ridge|Groove|Recess|Plinth|Shadow|None|Default|B0|B1|B1Ridge|B1None|B1Default}

 'F1'eWC'Form' 'EdgeStyle + Border'(50 50)(600 1200)('Coord' 'Pixel')

⍝ ─── Title + legend ────────────────────────────────────────────────
 'F1.TITLE'eWC'Label' 'EdgeStyle (rich) and Border (0/1) are INDEPENDENT properties'(10 10)(22 980)('FCol'(0 0 150))
 'F1.SUBTITLE'eWC'Label' 'Each row = one component. Last two columns set BOTH properties.'(35 10)(20 980)('FCol'(80 80 80))

