⍝ ─── SUBFORM row ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
⍝ Each SubForm gets a tinted background so its border is visible against
⍝ the form. A small Label is placed inside each SubForm as a child so the
⍝ variant is identifiable without relying on Caption (which the client
⍝ does not currently render for SubForm).
 'F1.RH_SF'      eWC'Label' 'SubForm'(370 10)(25 80)

 'F1.SF_Ridge'   eWC'SubForm'('Posn'(370 100))('Size'(80 80))('EdgeStyle' 'Ridge')   ('BCol'(245 245 255))
 'F1.SF_Ridge.lbl'eWC'Label' 'Ridge' (5 5)(20 70)

 'F1.SF_Groove'  eWC'SubForm'('Posn'(370 190))('Size'(80 80))('EdgeStyle' 'Groove')  ('BCol'(245 245 255))
 'F1.SF_Groove.lbl'eWC'Label' 'Groove'(5 5)(20 70)

